Paper: hep-th/9704184

Date: 1997-04-25

Title: Mirror Fermions in Noncommutative Geometry

Authors: F. Lizzi, G. Mangano, G. Miele and G. Sparano

Comments: 7 pages, LaTeX

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A13 (1998) 231-238

In a recent paper we pointed out the presence of extra fermionic degrees offreedom in a chiral gauge theory based on Connes Noncommutative Geometry. Herewe propose a mechanism which provides a high mass to these mirror states, sothat they decouple from low energy physics.